	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Shiru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">All this only means that you can't use arbitrary BPM and note placements, you need to use certain BPMs and quantize. Live play would require cleanup.</div>
<br />My music engine supports arbitrary BPMs in rows per minute. (It works like a Bresenham counter: add the bpm value to a 16-bit counter and wrap at 3606, starting a new row with each wrap.) But yes, live play would need a bit of quantization to move keypresses within one frame of the start of a row to the start of a row.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


